INSERT INTO `stories` VALUES (6,1,'Developer','modify ICT so that phone number groups are renamed to \"Destinaton Group\"s instead of \"Campaigns\"','Divorcing ICT from JTS is easier.','[\"All references to \'Campaign\' are replaced with \'Destination Group\',\",\"The \'Destination Group\' is stored at all times as \'dgrp\'.\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-03-22 13:10:12',0,''),(7,1,'Managing Director','a visitor session tracking mode.','I can record statistics on how long it takes people to call once they have been allocated a phone number.','[\"System provides a 1-1 mapping.\",\"Implemented as a per destination group which overrides normal allocation algorithm.\",\"Uses generated session identifier as sourceRef value.\",\"Stored in the D-Group configa table under the \'mode\' as \'sess\'.\",\"Default value for \'mode\' is \'norm\'.\",\"Session identifier stored in display log as \'sess\'.\",\"\",\"\",\"\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-03-22 13:10:12',0,''),(8,1,'Developer','An ICT cookie per Destination Group','There is no possibility of a phone number from one campaign being associated to a list from a different campaign.','[\"The Destination Group cookie should be called \\u2018ict.group_name\\u2019.Multiple values can be encoded as JSON into this cookie.Cookie should be encoded somehow to prevent tampering.\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-03-22 13:10:22',0,''),(9,1,'Developer','to extract the ICT source tag from the hreferer URL','I can use that instead of the current listing ID.','[\"Pulls the tag from a querystring var called \'ict\'.  Stores this in a cookie for the appropriate dgroup. Uses the principle of first click. If the cookie exists, the tag in the URL is ignored.The Source Ref value should be saved everywhere as \'srcref\'\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2010-03-22 13:10:22',0,''),(10,1,'Developer','to extract and store the javascript visitor referer','I can tell where the visitor came from and later use this data to discern the visitors raw search terms','[\"Data stored in JSON field as \'vreferrer\'\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(11,1,'Developer','to extract the HTTP referer.','we can pull the ict sourceref tag from the querystring.','[\"Stored in all cases as \'hreferer\'\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(13,4,'JUMP user','The graphs to illustrate when events occurred and what level they were at','we can see how events impacted a given campaign','[\"Graph has Solid line indicating account event\",\"Dashed line indicating campaign event\",\"Dotted line indicating adgroup event\",\"Other dotted line indicating adgroup event\",\"or, if lines don\'t work, then colours\",\"Black line for mulitple events on teh saame day.\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(14,4,'JUMP user','To see account level Events appear in teh event lies on all the dropdowns on each performance page and graph popups','I can see all relevant evetns at each level','[\"\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(15,5,'Technical Director','a detailed design document for proposed changes needed for the Google API v13 sunset + upgrading PPC Import to use NTL.','The design is signed off and partial changes are implemented before the sunset date of April 22nd  and PPC Import using NTL in Phase 2','[\"\\u2022Matrix of API call changes needed (Current call Vs New API calls)\",\"\\u2022Benefits of PPC Import using the NTL\",\"\\u2022How are we dealing with credit costs and what will change\",\"\\u2022Does it allow us to make batch bid cap changes and fixes the status issues when keyword snapshot is done. What else will this fix short and long term\",\"\"]','',0,'',0,0,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(17,7,'ICT client','To be able to pass arbitrary query string parameters via the destination URLs of the search networks and have ICT detect and use those as the sourcref value.','ICT can use any key:value pair on the querstring as sourcetag.sourceref value','[\"ICT allocate service detects, extracts and uses a querystring parameter as it\'s sourceref  value.\",\"This querystring comes from the HTTP referer when the javascript is called via a script tag on the client site.\",\"\"]','',10,'Detect sourceref',0,1,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(18,7,'Developer','To rename all instances of \'campaign\' to \'destination group\' and store any d-group related stuff in a json encoded cookie called \'ict.<dgroup_name>\'','we might have multiple destination groups per campaign/client/websites etc. and can store sourceref etc data in a cookie and not mix sourcerefs cross d-group','[\"Whatever is reference as \'campaign\' is now called \'destination group\'.\",\"The JSON stores the destination group as \'dgrp\'.\",\"Each destination group has it\'s own state table in the database, which is prefixed with the name \'state_\'. ie: \'state_monkeybadger\'.\",\"The destinaton group name should start with a letter and be ascii characters and not be longer than 10 chars.\",\"There is a cookie per d-group to store d-group based stuff called \'ict.<dgroup-name>\'\",\"Job consumer modified to support changes.\",\"Config update process modified to support changes.\",\"ICT Import modified to support changes\",\"Check to see if ttnc import needs changes or not.\",\"\"]','',25,'Changing \'campaign\' to \'destination group\'',0,13,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(19,7,'developer','to rename and restructure the campaign config table in the nas. Renamed to destination group config and change the buffertime column to be named \'config_options\' and store a JSON encoded string','We can add arbitrary config options to a d-group without changing database structure in the future.','[\"The table is renamed to \'destionation_group_config\'.\",\"The current buffer time column is renamed to \'config_options\' and is of a type suitable to support a JSON string,\",\"Config JSON contains a key of \'Mode\' which is either \'finite\' or \'infinite\'\",\"\"]','',15,'Campaign Config restructure',0,14,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(20,7,'Developer','To record the visitor referer (ie, the page that referred the visitor the page that the ICT javascript is installed on)','I can extract referrer data from the string, such as raw search terms.','[\"Client side javascript script tag contains querystring paramter and method to pass visitor referrer to NAS (via javascript script tag).\",\"Display log JSON config schema is modified to support vreferrer.\",\"Modify display log JSON config schema to use \'ua\' for user agent and \'ip\' for ip address.\",\"\"]','',12,'Record vreferer',0,15,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(21,7,'developer','to modify the import to store the imported data in native json rather then converting it into multiple columns. This data is also to be stored in MySQL.','I can then build other tables or views from this imported data.','[\"MySQL is used to store import data.\",\"Table has support for native json.\",\"Has it\'s own primary key auto-increment column which is not the same as live.\",\"It has a server ID column\",\"It has a date column.\",\"It has a JSON data column\",\"\"]','',15,'Import to MySQL',0,16,1,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,''),(22,7,'developer','the ability to store the display log in multiple tables which are rotated on a daily basis and import and API modified to support this change.','We can have a scalable display log system that can support multiple high traffic accounts.\n(Original Estimate: 30)','[\"tribbled creates one table per day named after the day it is creating it on.\",\"Import works.\",\"Recording state works.\",\"API modified to support these changes (specifying a table, returns a definated HTTP no content when you reach the end of the table)\",\"Import process modified to under